				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">A fair AoE change<a name="59123"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 26 04 1:18 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I know the topic is highly disputed.  Some Bards wanna see it made easier so they can get mad XP and others wanna see it nerfed because a pure AoE bard has a good chance of being a poor bard and making the class look bad.  Now I've AoE'd some in my Norathian life, but done ALL the rest as well but can see both sides of the argument.  This post is not meant to be a discussion on that topic.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, I was thinking, what did they have in mind when the songs were originally introduced?  Now I don't know the answer to that question, but I can speculate it was so bards could do damage to several mobs at once.... with some of the higher level AoE slowing as well..... but, I don't think they invisioned a bard running around with many many mobs in tow.  Sooooo.  Why not make the AoE song range like 50-60 and then reduce that range by 2 for every mob that the bard has agro on in the zone.  The numbers could be switched to whatever was desired.  You could easily adjust the numbers to make it so no more than X number of mobs could be kited and it would improve the usefulness of what I believe the original intent was.  Don't know how difficult it would be to program within there current design.... hehehe but it's computers.... it's doable.... just how difficult.  Dunno just an idea.  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
