				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A fair AoE change<a name="59161"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 26 04 3:45 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>If they were to nerf AoE kiting, I would suggest limiting the mobs affected to 4 mobs like with other classes that kite (i.e. quad kite).  In comparison to chant kiting high level mobs that you can't charm, I think AoE 4 mobs is still faster.  
<br />

<br />
CHANT kiting one mob
<br />
4 chants w/ IM2/TDoK lvl 65
<br />
4x140 = 560 per tick
<br />

<br />
AoE kiting 4 mobs
<br />
4 AoE songs w/ IM2/LotH lvl 65
<br />
49+46+78+98 = 271 x 4mobs = 1084 per tick
<br />
assuming every song lands.
<br />

<br />
Now if you are down to only landing about 50% of the damage per tick while AoE kiting, then you are basically doing the same amount of damage as chant kiting.
<br />

<br />
Now for charmable mobs, swarm kiting will probably the best kiting method.
<br />

<br />
I wonder how this damage per tick compares to other kiting classes (i.e. wizards, druids, necros, shamans...)</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
