				<td colspan="2"><span>
<br />
   A few things bug me about the whole AE ordeal:
<br />

<br />

<br />
1.  Why have AE at all if it isn't meant to be used?
<br />

<br />
2.  Why have zones that are clearly designed for AE purposes nerfed when all the non-AE classes whine?
<br />

<br />

<br />
   Another thing is that people like to complain without knowing the risk vs. reward.   I remember people bitching when an enchanter soloed the dragon in WL, when shamans were soloing WW dragons, etc.   Did these people even understand what it entailed to accomplish the task?  No.    Were tons of people of that particular class doing it?   No. 
<br />

<br />
   Everyone just wants to bring down another class that might be able to do more solo than the class they play. 
<br />

<br />
   If you can get a semi-decent group you can usually blow through more EXP/AA EXP than the average soloer can no problemo.
<br />

<br />
   I'm all for the bard class being more interesting to play in many aspects, but if they take away a lot of the soloing techniques I'll bet that the bard population will further dwindle.
<br />

<br />
   Regarding twisting, there are several articles that outline how many songs can in theory be twisted.    Even if you do some simple digging around you'll see that there aren't songs that will last in succession to allow for many to be sustained.
<br />

<br />

<br />
