				<td colspan="2"><span>One thing about 'limiting the mobs affected to 4 mobs like with other classes that kite'...
<br />
Actually all classes work the same, there are targeted AEs that alow you to stay outside of hit range, but those are limited to 4. (We got Desperate Dirge in that line of spells/songs.)
<br />
And there are point blankAEs that dont have a restriction in the number of targets.
<br />
Making a bard the only class with a restriction on PBAEs would be a bit strange in my opinion. The main difference between a bard and a caster is the bard's ability to run and cast at the same time, allowing him to cast, stay in AE range *and* not get hit. Restricting the number of targets on PBAE would unblance the game in a way it shouldn't be in my opinion. You would fix one mistake in game with another one.
<br />
From my point of view, the only real way to get rid of pure AE Bards would be (as I read in some posts already) fixing the Mob AI. For example programmers could code in some irregularities in mobs pathing. Let a mob run slower sometimes, let them chose different ways, let them pause etc. All this would easily dispatch any afk AE Kiter and make the game much less artificial and lively. (From a roleplaying point of view: The strange thing isnt a bard running and singing at the same time, the strange thing isnt a bard being able to harm a lot of monsters at the same time with his songs, the really strange thing is that not a single mob no matter how stupid it might be would always run after the bard in the same little circle.) One caster in a swarm can disrupt AE Kiting already when it stops at the wrong point of time and gets a bash in. Let melee mobs do the same and the problem should be solved.
<br />
My opinion on this.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
