				<td colspan="2"><span>
<br />

<br />
   I also see a lot of complaining about 'weekend bards'.   At this stage in the game, you should probably have about 5 alts if you've been playing for a long time.   Couple that in with lower levels being able to get crazy experience as compared to the original and first few expansions allows anyone with barely any skill at all to level to 65 in a very short amount of time.
<br />

<br />
   Why does it matter if low levels can or can't AE?   All these skills have been there for a long time and they scale to higher levels where in the last few years people have started to become concerned with them ( AE and charm ) because of the inherent mudflation that makes the mobs and PCs stronger.   As an enchanter I could charm effectively at level 12 and do quite well, but who cares?    The same goes for several other classes at lower levels.
<br />

<br />
   The majority of the players in this game are high level, so what benefit is there in trying to keep people in lower levels for extended periods of time?   Reaching 65 isn't some huge deal that should reward players greatly.   Pretty soon the cap will be level 70 and beyond and it won't take anymore skill than reaching level 2 did.
<br />

<br />
   To play the game as any class takes very little skill on average.   To accomplish certain things solo/duo or with smaller numbers does take cooperative skill, but to play as well as to not being recognized as a 'weekend' player of any class doesn't take much skill at all.
<br />

<br />
   If the majority of players want a nerf to bard AE then they should get a major positive change in return.
<br />

<br />
   If you look at the history of bards and AEing in general, I very highly doubt that anything will be done.    I don't anticipate a major change to how songs work, how bards AE as compared to any other class that has AE spells, etc.     These issues aren't new by any stretch of the imagination.
<br />

<br />
   Changing AI would be interesting, but at this point I highly doubt they'll be changing much of the AI for the standard zone exp mobs.   I recall them making sweeping changes in the AI to caster mobs a few years back and the first iteration was a disaster.</span></td>
