				<td colspan="2"><span>Brialla, uber bards do not twist 7 songs.  They are much smarter than that.  They twist 4 and usually 3 songs...with the smarts to know which 3 or 4 actually are needed at any time.  Have different song sets that can be quickly loaded since saved.
<br />

<br />
Do not strive to sing more than 4, strive to sing the right ones at the right times.  Strive to be able to pull singles, doubles, triples or whatever is needed.  Strive to be able to accomplish exceptional things with your fade and songs.
<br />

<br />
I respect bards that keep 5 songs up at once, but it is 10% of the job.  All the credit gets dumped in the toilet if they screw up the other 90%.
<br />

<br />
75% of the time I sing 3 solid.  25% I sing 4, knowing that I can afford to let 1 of the songs drop out once in a while (like mana).  Have to be picky about which three are constant and which gets the drop.  Rarely I sing 5, but it is only in groups where we are 200% better than what is needed.  To sing 5 in a group where you are actually needed for sucess is likely bad judgement and setting the group up for a wipe....unless there are 2 bards and you are the dps bard.
<br />

<br />
50% of your glory will come from consitant CC in various situations.  Soloing can get you self satisfaction occasionaly when you go deep in a kos dungeon and take out some targets that leave almost zero margin for error.
<br />

<br />
There are times when you might even save the day by taking a wack of mobs and using your skilled kiting tactics to get adds/mobs off the raid.  A highly skilled Kiter makes Mitheral Marr, and the BOT boss Agnarr and friends a joke raid.  (throw in the HOH cronies flag mobs as well)
<br />

<br />
Anyway, no one has ever said to me,  &quot;Moose you are slacking with a 3 song, can't you fit in 4 or 5?&quot;  &quot;Instead I hear...OMG I can not believe we are still alive after that mob gated and brought 6 friends back&quot;
<br />

<br />
I respect chanters yes, but when you don't have one..you are the CC.  Too bad they nerfed our Lull, but then again it separates the greats from the average.
<br />

<br />
Moose</span></td>
