				<td colspan="2"><span>First of all, spell haste doesnt affect bards. All songs have the very same cast time of 3 seconds with the exception of Dark Echo.
<br />
Well of course you can twist more songs using the different amounts of time songs last. For example a nice 5 song twist at lvl 60 is
<br />
1. Amplification
<br />
2. Verses of Victory
<br />
3. Niv's Harmonic
<br />
4. Cantata of Replenishment
<br />
5. Warsong of the Vah Shir
<br />
with extended duration on Amplification and WotVS
<br />
you can twist 1234523412345234....
<br />
And only drop WotVS for a few seconds before it land again.
<br />
This is what I still consider a 5 song twist.
<br />
Landing DoTs is another issue and you can land 5 constantly.
<br />
But singing Selo's Chorus, Clicking Levitate, using RoT and a few other things to get &quot;X Songs at the same&quot; isn't really what I consinder twisting.
<br />
What I consider twisting is what will be shown in the short duration buff box (and songs on enemies as long as they follow the short duration standards). 
<br />
With items such as <a target="_new" href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=5156">http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=5156</a> and it's insta clickie Niv's Melody of Preservation,
<br />
you can add another song to your twist. But please don't ask my why you would twist 7 songs else as for the purpose of showing off.
<br />
As Moose said, you detect a bards value seeing if he twists the right songs at the right time, not seeing how many he can twist at maximum if undisturbed.
<br />

