     I am still looking for the passage I know I have read in Eqdiva's forums somewhere, and I am going to assign the quote I am looking for to Kocho (although I very well could be wrong on the original poster!).  Because I cannot find the exact phrase, I am going to paraphrase what I seem to remember and hope someone remembers this particular reference.
<br />

<br />
   &lt;quote&gt; Who knew (in the beginning) what could be done by the bard &lt;/quote&gt;
<br />

<br />
I had gathered from several weeks of reading (prior) that she was referring to the Fansy days, the character that by all accounts seemed to have changed the rules of a server (and a game) for a variety of reasons. Since this character dates to 2001, 2 or so years after the start of Eq, I am a little unclear as to how an AoE nerf affects players that have played for five years. Forgive me, but I am coming from the position assuming that no-one at start-up of EQ knew the full potential of AoE versus a social-swarming type of MoB. I am also pre-luclin so am sure Aoe kiting was NOT common leveling technique.
<br />

<br />
   And from everything I have read of the Eq designers positions they never intended one class to level from 1 to 65 in the matter of Real Life hours. I have had bards brag lately to me they have gained 6 levels that day, I have tracked one, he seemed to be lying but you all offer a decent amount of opposite testimony.
<br />

<br />
I also have to disagree with any caster nerf that parralles a possible Bard nerf. No pure caster can cast and run at the same time, so it is, in my opinion, a moot argument. There is no way to compare a Bards casting abilities and nerfs to a pure caster because WE CAN RUN AND CAST. They cannot. One may argue creduously a nerf on a pure caster only by comparing them to a pure caster and then, secondarily, adding the comparison to a bard's exp leveling, and then one must begin taking in account other classes leveling time. 
<br />

<br />
   From what I can tell, I think bards may want to hush on the whole caster comparison lest they start being compared to Warriors instead<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />

