				<td colspan="2"><span>Moose, I admire your spunk but on the subject of AE songs I would strongly Disagree.  I see the removeable of Bard AE songs a result of level 60+ bards kiting all the mobs in a given zone.  I've seen an impressive 30 mob kiting done and sure was impressive but it is probably the reason why us lower level bard now pay the price.  
<br />

<br />
  My Bard just hit 39th was 1 gold into 38th when they removed AE kiting.  I never had any of this kiting of more than 4 mobs(heck kite 4 walrus in EW and if Temp wears off 4 hits can mean not only song disruption but stunning and a fast death).  
<br />

<br />
  I think the Bard AE songs should be fully restored up to 46th level.  Why 46th you ask? The Planes shouldn't be kite zones or have a balance like Magicians(Call of the Heroes) doesn't work in X zones.  Have AE songs no longer able to work on moving targets in X zones.  This would eliminate Bard out-balancing, and as for your comment on Bard's with XXX AA's... my main is a Magician... the most nerfed class in EQ 90% of a Magician's spells have limitation... summoned gear is usable by X class, Mod Rods and Mana Sticks are Lore Items, no Drop, AND have a 5 minute re-use timer on them, Rain Spells that cannot be used without killing yourself, LoS spells that can be blocked for partial or no damage from obstacles or other players, AA's such as MGB or Advanced Pet Discipline /pet nospell (oh yeah I summoned a fire pet now I want him to just melee...uh yeah and I want a bard to not play songs and become a Main tank). My old main is a Rogue SoS will be cool once I'm able to get it but NOTHING in game is as powerful as a Bard using Fading Memories. Wanna talk about the most POWERFUL AA in existance... you just aggro'd half a zone activate Selo's get a distance and Hit the Panic Button &quot;FADING MEMORIES&quot; poof you go invisible Drop ALL Aggro and can resume doing whatever you want.  
<br />

<br />
  I love playing my Bard and would love it if my AE songs once again had the normal effect and simply only affected stationairy targets in the Planes or Zones Sony feels AE songs become completely unbalancing.  Don't attack me yet.... these same zones ALSO would make Druid, Necro, and Wizard DoT's unfunctional as well... hey if Sony wants to PLAY FAIR then so be it Attack the druids(Sony's Favorite Class) and limit them as well.  But I do agree on most of what you say Moose just not on lower levels getting handicapped... this is when a Bard is learning to be Uber, once past 60 the fact that you are still playing your Bard means you have Uber skills and can kill more eefectively as a group player and AE more effectively stationairy targets.
<br />

<br />
My 2 Cents worth.
<br />

<br />
Dynarian 
<br />
39th Bard not yet worthy of a Magelo Account Portfolio</span></td>
